com.xilinx.rapidwright.design

Class Module

  • Object
    • com.xilinx.rapidwright.design.Module
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class Module
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Represents a collection of SiteInst and Net objects that can be instantiated as a ModuleInst. It serves as the prototype for a pre-implemented module.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • removeSiteInst

        public boolean removeSiteInst(String name)
        This method carefully removes an instance in a design with its pins and possibly nets. Nets are only removed if they are empty after removal of the instance's pins. This method CANNOT remove instances that are part of a ModuleInst.
        Parameters:
        name - The instance name in the module to remove.
        Returns:
        True if the operation was successful, false otherwise.
        Since:
        2018.2.0

      • isValidPlacement

        public boolean isValidPlacement(Site proposedAnchorSite,
                                Design design)
        Checks if the new proposed anchor site on this module is compatible with all of its internal sites. Optionally, it can also check if there are existing sites already placed at the proposed location.
        Parameters:
        proposedAnchorSite - The proposed new anchor site
        design - OPTIONAL - if non-null, will check against currently placed sites (TODO, also should check against PIPs)
        Returns:
        True if it is a valid, legal placement. False otherwise.
        Since:
        2020.2.5

      • getCorrespondingTile

        public static Tile getCorrespondingTile(Tile templateTile,
                                        Tile newAnchorTile,
                                        Tile originalAnchor,
                                        Tile[][] tiles)
        This method will calculate and return the corresponding tile of a module for a new anchor location for a given anchor location. This method is faster than Module.getCorrespondingTile(Tile, Tile, Tile) when doing many relocations of the same template. Calling code needs to cache the return value of newAnchorTile.getDevice().getTilesByRootName(templateTile.getRootName()) and supply it as parameter tiles.
        Parameters:
        templateTile - The tile in the module which acts as a template.
        newAnchorTile - This is the tile of the new anchor instance of the module.
        originalAnchor - Location of the anchor origin.
        tiles - The Tiles with the same Name Root as templateTile, as returned by Device.getTilesByRootName(String)
        Returns:
        The new tile of the module instance which corresponds to the templateTile, or null if none exists.
        Since:
        2020.2.6

      • getCorrespondingTile

        public static Tile getCorrespondingTile(Tile templateTile,
                                        Tile newAnchorTile,
                                        Tile originalAnchor)
        This method will calculate and return the corresponding tile of a module for a new anchor location for a given anchor location. When doing many relocations of the same template, consider using Module.getCorrespondingTile(Tile, Tile, Tile, Tile[][])
        Parameters:
        templateTile - The tile in the module which acts as a template.
        newAnchorTile - This is the tile of the new anchor instance of the module.
        originalAnchor - Location of the anchor origin.
        Returns:
        The new tile of the module instance which corresponds to the templateTile, or null if none exists.
        Since:
        2018.2.0

        Parameters:
